    "body": "I am having a similar issues. Both nodes are talking to bootnodes, but the two nodes are connecting to each other. \r\n\r\nIn general, is there documentation on network protocols of bootnodes? What is the mechanism of communication between bootnode and bootnode, bootnode to mining node, and mining node to mining node? I am setting up a private blockchain, and want to better understand how to configure the network topology.\r\n\r\n\r\nbootnode trace\r\n```\r\nTRACE[01-07|18:49:07] >> NEIGHBORS/v4                          addr=127.0.0.1:30555 err=nil\r\nTRACE[01-07|18:49:07] << FINDNODE/v4                           addr=127.0.0.1:30555 err=nil\r\nTRACE[01-07|18:49:09] >> NEIGHBORS/v4                          addr=127.0.0.1:30555 err=nil\r\nTRACE[01-07|18:49:09] << FINDNODE/v4                           addr=127.0.0.1:30555 err=nil\r\nTRACE[01-07|18:49:36] >> NEIGHBORS/v4                          addr=127.0.0.1:30444 err=nil\r\nTRACE[01-07|18:49:36] << FINDNODE/v4                           addr=127.0.0.1:30444 err=nil\r\nTRACE[01-07|18:49:40] >> NEIGHBORS/v4                          addr=127.0.0.1:30444 err=nil\r\nTRACE[01-07|18:49:40] << FINDNODE/v4                           addr=127.0.0.1:30444 err=nil\r\n```",
